#, java-format
#  ^^^^^^^^^^^ variable.annotation.po
msgid ""
"Within a String, a pair of single quotes can be used to quote any "
"arbitrary characters except single quotes. For example, pattern string "
"‘'{0}'’ represents string ‘{0}’, not a FormatElement. A single quote itself "
"must be represented by doubled single quotes '' throughout a String. For "
"example, pattern string ‘'{''}'’ is interpreted as a sequence of '{ (start "
"of quoting and a left curly brace), '' (a single quote), and }' (a right "
"curly brace and end of quoting), not '{' and '}' (quoted left and right "
"curly braces): representing string ‘{'}’, not ‘{}’."
msgstr ""
"A SubformatPattern is interpreted by its corresponding subformat, and "
"subformat-dependent pattern rules apply. For example, pattern string "
"{1,number,$'#',##} (SubformatPattern with underline) will produce a number "
#^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ constant.other.placeholder.po
"format with the pound-sign quoted, with a result such as: ‘$#31,45’. Refer "
"to each Format subclass documentation for details.\n"
"Any unmatched quote is treated as closed at the end of the given pattern. "
"For example, pattern string '{0} is treated as pattern '{0}'.\n"
"Any curly braces within an unquoted pattern must be balanced. For example, "
"‘ab {0} de’ and ‘ab '}' de’ are valid patterns, but ‘ab {0'}' de’, ‘ab } de’ "
"and ‘''{''’ are not. "

